You are writing BDD Playwright E2E tests for the ClassroomIO LMS dashboard. Apply the following hard-won lessons from debugging this codebase.

## Project structure

```
e2e/
├── features/        # Gherkin .feature files
├── steps/           # TypeScript step definitions
├── .features-gen/   # Auto-generated specs (DO NOT edit manually)
├── playwright.config.ts
└── global-setup.ts  # Port checks — services must be running before tests
```

Run tests: `pnpm test:e2e` from repo root.

## Critical rules

### 1. Always run from the repo root
`playwright test --config=e2e/playwright.config.ts` must be run from `/workspaces/classroomio/`, NOT from inside `e2e/`. Running from `e2e/` causes a "config not found" error.

### 2. Regenerate specs when feature files change
The `.features-gen/` directory is auto-generated by `playwright-bdd`'s `defineBddConfig()`. If a step is silently skipped (feature file was changed but specs not regenerated), delete `.features-gen/` and re-run. Stale specs are the #1 source of silent test failures.

```bash
rm -rf e2e/.features-gen/
pnpm test:e2e
```

### 3. Filling Svelte component textarea fields
`page.fill()` works for native `<input>` elements and Svelte components wrapping inputs (like `TextField`). However, for Svelte components wrapping `<textarea>` (like `TextArea`), `page.fill()` does NOT propagate through the component's `bind:value` chain to update the Svelte store. Use `page.evaluate()` with a native `InputEvent` instead:

```typescript
await page.evaluate((desc) => {
  const el = document.querySelector('[data-testid="my-textarea"]') as HTMLTextAreaElement | null;
  if (!el) throw new Error('element not found');
  el.focus();
  el.value = desc;
  el.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { bubbles: true, cancelable: false, inputType: 'insertText', data: desc }));
}, textValue);
```

This works because Svelte's compiled `bind:value` adds an `input` event listener that reads `textarea.value` synchronously when the event fires.

### 4. Wait for SvelteKit hydration before interacting
SvelteKit pages are server-rendered and then hydrated client-side. Carbon Design System's `<Theme>` component adds a `theme` attribute to `<html>` only after hydration. Use this as a reliable signal:

```typescript
async function waitForHydration(page: Page) {
  await page.waitForSelector('html[theme]', { timeout: 8000 });
}
```

Call `waitForHydration()` before any form interactions after `page.goto()`. Without it, clicks on submit buttons can fire before event handlers are attached, causing default browser form submissions (GET to `?`) instead of the Svelte handler.

### 5. Scoping Before/After hooks to relevant scenarios
Use Gherkin tags to scope cleanup hooks. Untagged `Before`/`After` hooks run before every scenario globally:

```typescript
// BAD: runs before login tests too
Before(async () => { await cleanupCourses(); });

// GOOD: only runs for @course scenarios
Before({ tags: '@course' }, async () => { await cleanupCourses(); });
```

Tag the scenario in the feature file:
```gherkin
@course
Scenario: Create a new course
```

### 6. Use timestamped titles for unique test data
Always append a timestamp to titles/names created during tests to avoid collisions and false-positive assertions:

```typescript
createdCourseTitle = `${title} ${Date.now()}`;
await page.fill('[data-testid="course-title-input"]', createdCourseTitle);
```

And assert against the timestamped value, not the generic Gherkin string:
```typescript
const actualTitle = createdCourseTitle || title;
await expect(page.getByText(new RegExp(actualTitle))).toBeVisible();
```

### 7. isLoading must always be reset
In Svelte form handlers, always reset `isLoading = false` on ALL early returns — both validation failures and database failures — otherwise the submit button stays permanently disabled:

```typescript
async function createCourse() {
  isLoading = true;
  const { hasError } = validateForm($store);
  if (hasError) { isLoading = false; return; }  // ← must reset

  const { data } = await supabase.from('...').insert(...).select();
  if (!data) { isLoading = false; return; }       // ← must reset
  ...
  isLoading = false;
}
```

### 8. data-testid attribute pattern
Components expose testId via an exported prop:
```svelte
export let testId = '';
// on the native element:
data-testid={testId || undefined}
```

Usage:
```svelte
<TextField testId="my-input" />
<TextArea testId="my-textarea" />
<PrimaryButton testId="my-button" />
```

Key test IDs in the dashboard:
| Element | `data-testid` |
|---------|--------------|
| Login email input | `login-email` |
| Login password input | `login-password` |
| Login submit button | `login-submit` |
| Create course button | `create-course-btn` |
| Course type option | `course-type-{SELF_PACED\|LIVE_CLASS}` |
| Next button (modal step 1) | `course-type-next` |
| Course title input | `course-title-input` |
| Course description textarea | `course-description-input` |
| Create/Finish button | `course-create-submit` |

### 9. Global timeout
The global test timeout is 10s (set in `playwright.config.ts`). This applies per-test, not per-step. Keep tests short. The 10s budget covers login (~3s) + navigation (~1s) + interactions (~2s) + assertion (~4s).

### 10. Services must be running
Tests fail fast if services are not running (port check in `global-setup.ts`):
- Dashboard: `http://localhost:5173`
- API: `http://localhost:3002`
- Supabase: `localhost:54321`

Start them before running: `supabase start`, then `pnpm dev`.
